def imshow(img):
  img = img.numpy()
  plt.axis('off')
  #plt.figure(figsize=(batch_size*4, 4))
  plt.imshow(np.transpose(img, (1, 2, 0)))
  plt.show()

In [0]:
class Mynet(nn.Module):
  def __init__(self):
    super().__init__()
    self.classifier = nn.Sequential(
        nn.Linear(784, 48),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.Linear(48, 24),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.Linear(24, 10)
    )
  
  def forward(self, x):
    x = x.view(x.size(0), -1)
    x = self.classifier(x)
    return x
In [0]:
class Mynet_batchNorm(nn.Module):
  def __init__(self):
    super().__init__()
    self.classifier = nn.Sequential(
        nn.Linear(784, 48),
        nn.BatchNorm1d(48),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.Linear(48, 24),
        nn.BatchNorm1d(24),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.Linear(24, 10)
    )
  
  def forward(self, x):
    x = x.view(x.shape[0], -1)
    x = self.classifier(x)
    return x
In [0]:
device = torch.device('cuda:0')
In [0]:
model_Mynet = Mynet()
model_bn = Mynet_batchNorm()
model_Mynet = model_Mynet.to(device)
model_bn = model_bn.to(device)
In [0]:
print(model_Mynet)
print(model_bn)

Mynet(
  (classifier): Sequential(
    (0): Linear(in_features=784, out_features=48, bias=True)
    (1): ReLU()
    (2): Linear(in_features=48, out_features=24, bias=True)
    (3): ReLU()
    (4): Linear(in_features=24, out_features=10, bias=True)
  )
)
Mynet_batchNorm(
  (classifier): Sequential(
    (0): Linear(in_features=784, out_features=48, bias=True)
    (1): BatchNorm1d(48, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (2): ReLU()
    (3): Linear(in_features=48, out_features=24, bias=True)
    (4): BatchNorm1d(24, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (5): ReLU()
    (6): Linear(in_features=24, out_features=10, bias=True)
  )
)

loss_fn = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()
opt_mynet = opt.Adam(model_Mynet.parameters())
opt_bn = opt.Adam(model_bn.parameters())

In [0]:
epochs=2
loss_arr_mynet, loss_arr_bn = [], []
for epoch in range(epochs):
  for i, data in enumerate(trainloader, 0):
    inputs, labels = data
    inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device)
    
    opt_mynet.zero_grad()
    output_mynet = model_Mynet(inputs)
    #_, pred = torch.max(output_mynet, 1)
    loss_mynet = loss_fn(output_mynet, labels)
    loss_mynet.backward()
    opt_mynet.step()
    
    opt_bn.zero_grad()
    output_bn = model_bn(inputs)
    #_, pred = torch.max(output_bn, 1)
    loss_bn = loss_fn(output_bn, labels)
    loss_bn.backward()
    opt_bn.step()
    
    loss_arr_mynet.append(loss_mynet.item())
    loss_arr_bn.append(loss_bn.item())
    
    if i%20 == 0:
      model_Mynet.eval()
      model_bn.eval()
      inputs = inputs.view(inputs.size(0), -1)
      temp = model_Mynet.classifier[0](inputs)
      temp = model_Mynet.classifier[1](temp)
      temp = model_Mynet.classifier[2](temp)
      temp = temp.to('cpu')
      temp = temp.detach().numpy().ravel()
      sns.distplot(temp, kde=True, color='b', label="without bn")
      
      inputs = inputs.view(inputs.size(0), -1)
      temp_bn = model_bn.classifier[0](inputs)
      temp_bn = model_bn.classifier[1](temp_bn)
      temp_bn = model_bn.classifier[2](temp_bn)
      temp_bn = model_bn.classifier[3](temp_bn)
      temp_bn = model_bn.classifier[4](temp_bn)
      temp_bn = temp_bn.to('cpu')
      temp_bn = temp_bn.detach().numpy().ravel()
      
      sns.distplot(temp_bn, kde=True, color='r', label="with bn")
      plt.title("%d : loss without bn= %0.2f, loss with bn=%0.2f" % (i, loss_mynet.item(), loss_bn.item()))
      plt.legend()
      plt.show()

      model_Mynet.train()
      model_bn.train()
  plt.plot(loss_arr_mynet, 'b', label='Normal')
  plt.plot(loss_arr_bn, 'r', label='BN')
  plt.show()
In [0]:
def evaluation(dataloader):
  total_net, correct_net, total_bn, correct_bn =0,0, 0, 0
  for data in dataloader:
    inputs, labels = data
    inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device)
    output_mynet = model_Mynet(inputs)
    _, pred = torch.max(output_mynet, 1)
    total_net+= labels.shape[0]
    correct_net += (pred == labels).sum().item()
    
    output_bn = model_bn(inputs)
    _, pred = torch.max(output_bn, 1)
    total_bn+= labels.shape[0]
    correct_bn += (pred == labels).sum().item()
    
    return 100*correct_net/total_net, 100*correct_bn / total_bn

In [0]:
N = 50
noise = 0.3

X_train = torch.unsqueeze(torch.linspace(-1, 1, N), 1)
Y_train = X_train + noise * torch.normal(torch.zeros(N, 1), torch.ones(N, 1))

X_test = torch.unsqueeze(torch.linspace(-1, 1, N), 1)
Y_test = X_test + noise * torch.normal(torch.zeros(N, 1), torch.ones(N, 1))

plt.scatter(X_test.data.numpy(), Y_test.data.numpy(), c='yellow', alpha=0.5, label='test')

In [0]:
model = nn.Sequential(
    nn.Linear(1, 100),
    nn.ReLU(),
    nn.Linear(100, 50),
    nn.ReLU(),
    nn.Linear(50, 10)
)

model_dropout = nn.Sequential(
    nn.Linear(1, 100),
    nn.Dropout(0.5),
    nn.ReLU(),
    nn.Linear(100, 50),
    nn.Dropout(0.5),
    nn.ReLU(),
    nn.Linear(50, 10)
)
In [0]:
loss_fn = nn.MSELoss()
opt = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters())
opt_dropout = torch.optim.Adam(model_dropout.parameters())
In [57]:
max_epochs = 1000

for epoch in range(max_epochs):
    
    pred = model(X_train) # look at the entire data in a single shot
    loss = loss_fn(pred, Y_train)
    opt.zero_grad()
    loss.backward()
    opt.step()
    
    pred_dropout = model_dropout(X_train)
    loss_dropout = loss_fn(pred_dropout, Y_train)
    opt_dropout.zero_grad()
    loss_dropout.backward()
    opt_dropout.step()
    
    
    if epoch % 50 == 0:
        
        model.eval()
        model_dropout.eval()
        
        test_pred = model(X_test)
        test_loss = loss_fn(test_pred, Y_test)
        
        test_pred_dropout = model_dropout(X_test)
        test_loss_dropout = loss_fn(test_pred_dropout, Y_test)
        
        plt.scatter(X_train.data.numpy(), Y_train.data.numpy(), c='purple', alpha=0.5, label='train')
        plt.scatter(X_test.data.numpy(), Y_test.data.numpy(), c='yellow', alpha=0.5, label='test')
        plt.plot(X_test.data.numpy(), test_pred.data.numpy(), 'r-', lw=3, label='normal')
        plt.plot(X_test.data.numpy(), test_pred_dropout.data.numpy(), 'b--', lw=3,  label='dropout')
        
        plt.title('Epoch %d, Loss = %0.4f, Loss with dropout = %0.4f' % (epoch, test_loss, test_loss_dropout))
        
        plt.legend()

        model.train()
        model_dropout.train()
        
        plt.pause(0.05)
